@q0Very good. With the Core and the Capacitor (Solar) and at least one solar panel you can start your base. Keep in mind that the Capacitor has to charge first. Depending on the position of your solar panels<color=#ffae00>*</color> , it may take some time until the first power arrives.  On the main page and the STATISTICS tab of the control panel (<color=#44ff00>P</color>) you can see the current production rate and the consumption rate.  It is best to plan now to install more solar panels, because your energy consumption will increase quickly! 
*Efficiency: Yellow LEDs = current, influenced by weather/day/night; Green = day average, influenced by placement  @p9 If you have not yet completed the other components (window, door, stairs and roof repair), you can proceed with this.  

If you want to activate the second part of the Guided Tutorial, select the corresponding answer below to read the instructions!

